Prophecies of Elisha","slug":"event-186","score":11}],"links":[{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recutYqTqunXPJKQO","label":"part of"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recKGwJpH24g67ZTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recbHLkz06CSe3C4K","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"reco82mzy0XTzaOgv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recdMHFSmu222VnJG","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recJK76HLZSOzxTWW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"rec5dSSsOutWlH2fW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recMk8e2xt1Lf5HKz","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recE8QW1xGYrhGwR4","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recEP3QZ3HUmIkv4Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recRiyMlpGQNCIZvm","label":"event"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recD1Gv4SKNFG3zPa","label":"event"},{"source":"recrHbxxa3CWH42HL","target":"recCh323mcqdG01EW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recVR7HjALLzDdcwM","ref":"2Kgs.2.1","text":"And it came to pass, when the LORD would take up Elijah into heaven by a whirlwind, that Elijah went with Elisha from Gilgal.","year":-896},{"id":"recuJktD41rvyisNo","ref":"2Kgs.2.2","text":"And Elijah said unto Elisha, Tarry here, I pray thee; for the LORD hath sent me to Bethel. And Elisha said unto him, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. So they went down to Bethel.","year":-896},{"id":"recutk7QzdUqI10jU","ref":"2Kgs.2.3","text":"And the sons of the prophets that were at Bethel came forth to Elisha, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the LORD will take away thy master from thy head to day? And he said, Yea, I know it; hold ye your peace.","year":-896},{"id":"rec0sC2ZNqZjbI1hg","ref":"2Kgs.2.4","text":"And Elijah said unto him, Elisha, tarry here, I pray thee; for the LORD hath sent me to Jericho. And he said, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. So they came to Jericho.","year":-896},{"id":"recLAwimathhtC2DX","ref":"2Kgs.2.5","text":"And the sons of the prophets that were at Jericho came to Elisha, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the LORD will take away thy master from thy head to day? And he answered, Yea, I know it; hold ye your peace.","year":-896},{"id":"recZsyxyvqspZOj06","ref":"2Kgs.2.6","text":"And Elijah said unto him, Tarry, I pray thee, here; for the LORD hath sent me to Jordan. And he said, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. And they two went on.","year":-896},{"id":"recguhFV1tokvEYJE","ref":"2Kgs.2.7","text":"And fifty men of the sons of the prophets went, and stood to view afar off: and they two stood by Jordan.","year":-896},{"id":"recmkd94FTRXGyVDT","ref":"2Kgs.2.8","text":"And Elijah took his mantle, and wrapped it together, and smote the waters, and they were divided hither and thither, so that they two went over on dry ground.","year":-896}]}
